#. <section class="sutta" id="sn17.6"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn17.6:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 17"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 17"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.6:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga"
msgstr "1. The First Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 6. Asanisutta → asanivicakkasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn17.6:0.3"
msgid "6. Asanisutta"
msgstr "6. A Bolt of Lightning"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn17.6:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn17.6:1.2"
msgid "“Dāruṇo, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe … adhigamāya."
msgstr "“Possessions, honor, and popularity are brutal …"

#. VAR: sekhaṃ → sekhaṃ (s1-3, km) | taṃ sekhaṃ (pts1-2, mr) | km sekhaṃ (?)
#. VAR: anupāpuṇātu → anupāpuṇāti (pts1-2, mr)
msgctxt "sn17.6:1.3"
msgid ""
"Kaṃ, bhikkhave, asanivicakkaṃ āgacchatu, sekhaṃ appattamānasaṃ "
"lābhasakkārasiloko anupāpuṇātu."
msgstr ""
"Who should be struck by lightning? A trainee who comes into possessions, "
"honor, and popularity before they achieve their heart’s desire."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn17.6:2.1"
msgid "Asanivicakkanti kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasilokassetaṃ adhivacanaṃ."
msgstr "‘Lightning strike’ is a term for possessions, honor, and popularity."

msgctxt "sn17.6:2.2"
msgid "Evaṃ dāruṇo kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko … pe …"
msgstr "So brutal are possessions, honor, and popularity. …”"

msgctxt "sn17.6:2.3"
msgid "evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn17.6:2.4"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
